p: The yield percentage of EO extracted from the AW of T. ammi was 0.28 mg/mL. The qualitative and quantitative compositions of the EO are presented in Table 1. Approximately, 20 compounds, representing 99.8% area of the EO, were identified. Gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) analyses showed that the main constituent of EO was thymol (78.08%), followed by carvacrol (8.20%) and Mcarvotanacetone (6.50%).
